headline: Analog Devices Stock Rises. The Industry Has Hit Bottom, Analysts Say.
summary: Analog Devices may be investors’ best bet in, well, analog devices, analysts at Cantor Fitzgerald say.  The Cantor Fitzgerald team issued an upbeat near-term outlook for the analog semiconductor industry, arguing that stocks in the group, which includes names like  Texas Instruments ON Semiconductor Microchip Technology  and  NXP Semiconductors  has hit bottom.  Analog Devices  was the headliner.
